result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Edward E Adams in court with Attorney Nicholas Martinez.  David John Behm appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  This case is dismissed and read-in for Defendant's plea to Case #15CM2229.
Court received information from Wisconsin Community Services regarding defendant's compliance/non-compliance.

Defendant Edward E Adams in court with attorney Nicholas Martinez.  Brian J. Juech appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Atty Martinez enters not guilty plea to charges on Amended complaint on 15CM2229. Atty Martinez requests a date in 45 days to review case. Court quashes capias on 15CM2229 based on Defendant's appearance. Court addresses WCS letter. Bail remains as fixed.  Hearing scheduled for February 1, 2016 at 10:30 am.

Absolute sobriety, defendant is not to possess or consume any alcohol.  Defendant is not to use/possess any controlled substances without a valid prescription and take as prescribed.  Defendant ordered to SCRAM monitoring.  Defendant to pay costs associated with SCRAM monitoring.  Defendants who can not  pay will be required to follow an enhanced level of direct supervision requirements as established by WCS.  WCS will notify the Court.  Defendant to have SCRAM installed within one business day from today.

Defendant Edward E Adams in court, in custody, with attorney Nicole Masnica for attorney Jess Martinez.   Abbey Nickolie appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant is eligible for State Public Defender representation.  An attorney will be appointed.  NOT GUILTY PLEA ENTERED.  Hearing scheduled for December 18, 2015 at 10:30 am.
Waukesha County Pretrial Screening Services Report by Wisconsin Community Services filed.
